msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/selfhosting.md:5
msgid ""
"#### Definition **Self-hosting** is having a server at home in order to host "
"personnal data and services on it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/selfhosting.md:8
msgid ""
"#### Administrator responsibilities Self-hosting implies responsibilities, "
"if you want to host a website, [emails](email) and have [an instant "
"messaging system](XMPP) running, the server needs to stay online all the "
"time, 24/7."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/selfhosting.md:10
msgid ""
"Problems can happen and the server could become unavailable: a power outage, "
"Internet access loss, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/selfhosting.md:12
msgid ""
"If you use the [email system](email_en) and your server becomes unavailable, "
"emails destined to the server will be re-sent under 3 to 7 days."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/selfhosting.md:17
msgid ""
"#### Self-hosting contraints * Slow transfer speed. With ADSL, upload is "
"approximately 1/10 of the rate of download. For instance: 1 Mb/s download "
"speed would give an upload speed of 100 kb/s; * Availability must be 24/7; * "
"Move;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/jb/Projects/Simon/content/pages/administrator/selfhosting.md:22
msgid ""
"#### Self-hosting issues * Anonymity, private life; * Reappropriation of "
"personnal data and services; * Decentralization, distributed networks;"
msgstr ""

